Looking at the code, I can see it's using a `List` component with `LazyForEach`. The linting rule `@performance/hp-arkui-set-cache-count-for-lazyforeach-grid` requires setting `cachedCount` on the `LazyForEach` to improve performance by pre-caching items.

The fix is to add `.cachedCount(1)` after the `LazyForEach` block and before the `.width('100%')` method chain. A value of 1 is appropriate for a contact list as it caches one item beyond the visible area, which helps with smooth scrolling without consuming excessive memory.

